        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The primary goal of the proposed ALMA observations is to image the innner circumstellar environment around GW Ori in the Band 7 continuum and to detect the dynamical imprint of the companion near the disc gap at 110 mas separation from the star. The 0.85mm flux has been measured by Mathieu et al. (1995, AJ 109, 2655) with JCMT to 1 Jy and we would like to image structures within 0.4" (which allows us to cover structures twice as extended as the expected outer disc gap radius at 0.1"). It is possible that the disc is slight more extended and we are aware that more extended structures in the outer disc would be resolved out.

We would like to achieve a synthesized beam of 40 mas and a high SNR of 200, which sets our desired sensitivity per pointing to 0.032 mJy.  Using the observing tool, we estimate the required total observing time for our program to 1.0 hrs (including calibration). This will ensure that we will also have signficant sky rotation for aperture synthesis.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The focus of our observations is on high-contrast continuum imaging in ALMA band 7. We do not include spectral lines due to sensitivity considerations.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We would like to image the edge near the outer gap region at 0.1" separation from the star. Therefore, we will be able to capture all relevant structures in the 0.48" field-of-view that will be provided by the requested setup. It is possible that the disc might extend somewhat further, but it does not compromise our science goal if any extended structures would be resolved out.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
